messages.message:
Brian
hi

hey!
what's new with you?

Brian
I finally graduated and got a job in phoenix.
You?

congrats!
Where are you working?
I work at US Airways in Tempe.

Brian
really? what do you do for US Airways?

revenue management
I figure out how much demand there is on flights
and how much to overbook

Brian
oh cool.  sounds like lots of math.

yep 
and what do you do?

Brian
I am doing software development for 2 startups, my day job is for a company EPIC Research & Diagnostics.  We are developing a machine and algorithm that takes a picture of your finger tip's energy field and can tell you about a bunch of different parts of your body.
We are seeking FDA approval to use it as a medical diagnostics device.  So we have to prove statistically that the algorithm works.  Its voodoo to me. haha
WOW, cool!

Brian
yeah, I enjoy it.
You hair is so dark!  Did you dye it?
I just noticed your profile picture.

yeah it does look dark, eh?
I think it's getting a little darker

Brian
I just started listening to this: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zy7V5DXUhCM
I have dyed it with temp dye a few times which makes it a little darker still

Brian
It looks nice.  your eyes really stand out.
where do you live?

Brian
Scottsdale
Raintree and 92nd
you?
near ASU

Brian
neato

hey well I have to run
It's good to hear from you, have a good evening

Brian
ok! nice to catch up, I didn't even realize you lived in the same city.  We should get lunch sometime.
goodnight
hi!

Brian
I'm home sick today 
how are you?

aw, feel better
I'm doing really well

Brian
thanks!
oh yeah?  what's the most fun you've had lately?
Well, no big trips lately, but I'm dating a really good guy, and that's been fun!

Brian
oh good!  how did you meet?
I've been single for a while, kind of hard to meet people outside of school.
We met at a church potluck

Brian
Oh good call.  My mom keeps trying to get me to go to this church group.

heheh
Where does your mom live?

Brian
We live in north scottsdale, she lives in greyhawk, i live by frank loyd wright
oh that's nice and close

Brian
yeah.
Where are you working again?

Brian
for a medical start up like 5 minutes away on princess rd.  EPIC research & diagnostics.
you like it?

Brian
working on a GSR (galvanic skin response) system that can read your fingertips and is supposed to tell you about a bunch of different parts of your body.
yeah it's interesting.  I'm learning a lot about startups.  And I am learning a lot in my field.
Still working for US Airways?

that is interesting
yep, I like it a lot

Brian
that's good!  not everyone gets to do something they enjoy.

yeah, I'm pretty lucky. Works been a little slow lately, but it's starting to pick up again
Hey I have to run, it's good to hear from you
Have a good evening

Brian
you too

Brian
hi!

Brian
Hi
